fwprop.entryDesc:
Set AreYouAliveSrc to zero and
AreYouAliveStart to the current time

Retrieve an OutComponent of
type (17,1) from the OutFactory

Set outcome of Start
Action to 'Failure' with failure
code VER_REP_CR_FD

Set outcome of Start
Acton to 'Success'

fwprop.note:
The OutComponent encapsulates the
(17,1) command to the target application.

This procedure is run by the Start Action of the
command (17,3) to perform a connection test to a
target application. The identifier of the target application
is a parameter of the (17,3) command.

The identifier of the target
application is legal if it
is in: isAppProcAliveDestList

The destination of the (17,1)
report is the target application

fwprop.entryDesc:
Retrieve an OutComponent of
type (17,4) from the OutFactory

fwprop.note:
The OutComponent encapsulates
the response to the (17,3) command

fwprop.guardDesc:
Identifier of target 
application is legal

fwprop.smNotes: This procedure must be attached to the InCommand component which implements the (17,3) command. The procedure reports an outcome. For this purpose, the descriptor of the (17,3) command must be loaded as 'procedure data' in the procedure (this is done using function ::FwPrSetData). The procedure therefore assumes its procedure data to be an object of type FwSmDesc_t representing an InCommand and it deposits its outcome in the 'outcome' field of the InCommand descriptor.
